The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, March 19, 2004 				 LG drive to boost AC sales
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, March 18: LG Electronics India (LGEIL) has beefed up its after-sales services for air-conditioners to capture a larger market share.																								The company is organising training programmes for local air-conditioner mechanics.																								Salil Kapoor, national head of room air-conditioner division, LGEIL, said, The move will facilitate a strong front-end interface with the customer. We have completed the first round of training for 1600 mechanics. Another 400 will be trained during the year.																								The company spends around Rs 5-6 crore on training exercises. The air-conditioner division currently contributes 20 per cent of the total turnover. 																								The firm is aiming to capture 40 per cent of the air-conditioner market. 
